00:03:28.230 --> 00:03:29.600
Pinto.

00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:32.470
Phil was heavily into
fire crackers, gunpowder,

00:03:32.470 --> 00:03:36.180
rocket engines, and all
things that are explosive.

00:03:36.180 --> 00:03:39.220
So it was natural that after his
undergraduate work at Harvard,

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:42.320
he moved to the Lick
Observatory at UC Santa Cruz

00:03:42.320 --> 00:03:45.330
to do graduate work on
supernova, the largest

00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:47.350
explosions in the universe.

00:03:47.350 --> 00:03:50.960
And just as he was finishing his
dissertation, remarkably still

00:03:50.960 --> 00:03:53.680
with all his fingers,
the brightest supernova

00:03:53.680 --> 00:03:57.180
in 400 years exploded
in a nearby galaxy.

00:03:57.180 --> 00:04:00.000
Being at Santa Cruz, this
had nothing to do with pot.

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:01.528
