plasmas in the laboratory,

00:04:21.339 --> 00:04:23.960
techniques for computer
modeling in astrophysics,

00:04:23.960 --> 00:04:25.980
and most certainly
on the formation

00:04:25.980 --> 00:04:29.690
of large-scale structures
in the universe.

00:04:29.690 --> 00:04:33.140
Phil is one of the founders
of the Large Synoptic Survey

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:34.260
Telescope.

00:04:34.260 --> 00:04:39.150
This is the most important
new endeavor in astronomy,

00:04:39.150 --> 00:04:42.130
as described by the National
Academy of Sciences.

00:04:42.130 --> 00:04:45.080
It's an 8.4-meter telescope,
whose primary mirror is

00:04:45.080 --> 00:04:48.620
